            h2 How can the American Gut Project community scientifically test their ideas?

            div(style="margin-top:40px;") The American Gut Project community has intuitions about how one's gut affects their health.  

            br
            h4 People's tracking can yield incorrect/incomplete results

            div(style="margin-top:20px;") To test such intuitions, people often make some changes in their lifestyle, and then observe the effects of those changes. For example, consider Janet, who thinks that her habit of taking a probiotic every morning improves her energy levels throughout the day. To test this, she switches to not taking a probiotic for a week and tracks how she feels every day. But her measurements show that she's actually getting more done after avoiding her daily dose of probiotics! Janet realises that there could be many factors that could be affecting her energy levels - she could’ve been staying up late binge watching that latest show, or she might have been eating different food, or it could be that she increased her soda intake which has high amounts of caffeine.

            div(style="margin-top:20px;") Such unsystematic tracking activities often yield incorrect results that can be frustrating. #[i So what could Janet do to know for sure that taking a probiotic could really help improve her daily energy levels?]

